tted to carry additional equipment, house crew and there is also a desalinization system that is made for the Titan 200 platform. We looked at Cape Winds proposal, talked to a lot of the designers and environmental consultants who worked on the project, even met with Doug Hines in DC where he had been called to speak before a congressional panel about these wind platforms. Any offshore project we pursue will use the Titan 200 Wind Platform. We are focusing on acquisition of Frying Pan Shoals tower to get an offshore site in a prime wind location. If USACE will allow us to turn the old tower into an artificial reef we'll replace the old tower with a new Titan 200 on the same lease site. I encourage you to google up Offshore Wind Platforms of Texas. I'm sure Doug can answer any questions you or anyone else may have. There is also some cost comparison information on the site that is useful. Sincerely, Bob Getchell Noreaster Energy Partners

